               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary"> Historian Sharaf al-Dīn ʻAlī Yazdī (d. 1454)
                     completed his <title>Ẓafarnāmah</title> (Book of Victory) in 828 AH (1424–1425
                     CE) for the Timurid prince and bibliophile, Ibrāhīm Sulṭān b. Shāh Rukh
                     (1394–1435). He chronicles the life and exploits of his patron's grandfather,
                     Central Asian ruler Tīmūr (b. 1336, r. 1370–1405), founder of the Timurid
                     dynasty (1370–1507), and his son and successor Shāh Rukh Mīrzā (b. 1337, r.
                     1405–1447). This manuscript, completed in <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari"
                        when="1501">907 AH (1501 CE)</date> comprises a fairly early redaction of the
                     text, completed just over fifty years after the author's death. </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_829-item1">
